[2026-06-06 22:35] [default]
Q: does it currently look adoptable by other users?
A: No. The codebase is tightly coupled to macOS (launchd service in `lifecycle.py`, zsh PATH patching, `~/.config/askr` hardcoded paths) and assumes Claude Code IDE with specific `.claude/settings.json` hook integration. It's also missing critical files (`user_prompt_submit.py`, `pipeline.py`, `snapshot.py`) that are referenced but not provided. A new user would hit immediate blockers on non-Mac systems and incomplete dependencies.
